[14.0, "o", "[1;32m>[0m What is DateRules.MonthStart() вЂ” does it respect trading calendars?\r\n"]
[14.5, "o", "\r\n"]
[15.3, "o", "Yes. In LEAN, [1mDateRules.MonthStart()[0m fires on the first [1mtrading day[0m of each\r\n"]
[15.6, "o", "month, not the first calendar day. It uses the exchange calendar of the\r\n"]
[15.9, "o", "first security in the algorithm, so weekends and holidays are skipped.\r\n"]
[16.2, "o", "\r\n"]
[16.5, "o", "[90mвљ   Gotcha:[0m DateRules.MonthStart([33mn[0m) treats [33mn[0m as a Symbol, not a day\r\n"]
[16.8, "o", "   offset. To offset by days use MonthStart([33m\"SPY\"[0m, [33m2[0m) instead.\r\n"]
